1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,506
(This drama complied with production
guidelines for filming child actors,)

2
00:00:01,507 --> 00:00:03,074
(and some scenes used
generative AI technology.)

3
00:00:03,786 --> 00:00:06,213
(Episode 2)

4
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,333
(Na Ji Ni)

5
00:00:26,979 --> 00:00:30,174
- Hi, I'm Do Do Hee.
- I'm Na Ji Ni.

6
00:00:30,240 --> 00:00:32,707
- Let's be friends.
- Okay.

7
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:08,740
Is it really that hard to beat Na Ji Ni?

8
00:01:12,464 --> 00:01:17,007
Can't you come in first just once?
You idiot.

9
00:01:18,007 --> 00:01:22,140
Why are you always stuck in second place?

10
00:01:22,694 --> 00:01:25,560
What am I supposed to tell your father?
That we don't have enough money?

11
00:01:25,760 --> 00:01:27,427
That I didn't work hard enough?

12
00:01:27,627 --> 00:01:29,927
You're the problem!

13
00:01:30,510 --> 00:01:33,227
Mom, I'm sorry.

14
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:34,728
You drive me crazy.

15
00:01:41,194 --> 00:01:42,325
Na Ji Ni!

16
00:01:54,760 --> 00:01:56,827
They say kids take after their parents.

17
00:01:56,894 --> 00:01:58,427
That's what my grandmother says.

18
00:01:58,794 --> 00:02:01,160
Your parents shape half your life,
and your character shapes your destiny.

19
00:02:02,727 --> 00:02:05,160
Guess it's my fate
to be born to a psycho like her.

20
00:02:06,560 --> 00:02:10,994
Na Ji Ni, do me a huge favor
and come in second for once.

21
00:02:11,660 --> 00:02:14,284
No one's yanking your hair
to make you come in first, right?

22
00:02:14,394 --> 00:02:16,394
About my grades,

23
00:02:16,627 --> 00:02:18,194
I wasn't always first either.

24
00:02:18,260 --> 00:02:20,327
That's not helping, Na Ji Ni.

25
00:02:31,094 --> 00:02:32,827
My mom even faked her education.

26
00:02:33,460 --> 00:02:34,760
She never went
to Seoul National University.

27
00:02:35,394 --> 00:02:36,927
That's why she's even worse.

28
00:02:37,160 --> 00:02:39,927
She thinks I have to get into SNU
to save her pride.

29
00:02:41,827 --> 00:02:43,027
You know my dad,

30
00:02:44,294 --> 00:02:45,394
right?

31
00:02:45,460 --> 00:02:47,894
Yeah, isn't he a diplomat?

32
00:02:48,027 --> 00:02:50,294
My dad's first love is a spokesperson.

33
00:02:50,660 --> 00:02:53,494
She's always on the news.
She's really impressive.

34
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:57,227
No wonder the psycho
at my house goes crazy.

35
00:03:06,660 --> 00:03:08,094
What you saw today stays between us.

36
00:03:08,527 --> 00:03:10,527
If word gets out, I'll kill you.

37
00:03:11,094 --> 00:03:13,227
You're not the only one with secrets.

38
00:03:14,268 --> 00:03:16,927
I have one too.

39
00:03:18,360 --> 00:03:19,794
Come to my house.

40
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:30,427
Your mom is the cellist, Na Se Ri?

41
00:03:33,182 --> 00:03:34,360
Isn't she single?

42
00:03:35,227 --> 00:03:37,027
The beautiful, single cellist?

43
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,027
Your mom's awesome.

44
00:03:39,094 --> 00:03:40,460
I see.

45
00:03:41,127 --> 00:03:42,827
Then why doesn't she come to school?

46
00:03:42,960 --> 00:03:44,560
It'd cause a scene if she did.

47
00:03:46,376 --> 00:03:48,794
You were so cute!

48
00:03:48,927 --> 00:03:50,394
So pretty!

49
00:03:55,094 --> 00:03:58,393
She had a recital recently.

50
00:03:58,394 --> 00:03:59,394
I know.

51
00:03:59,527 --> 00:04:01,927
My parents went too.

52
00:04:01,994 --> 00:04:03,026
(Cheongrok Arts High School classmates)

53
00:04:03,027 --> 00:04:04,027
(Park Eun Hyeong, Lee Han In)

54
00:04:04,094 --> 00:04:05,260
Who are they?

55
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:07,327
They're our art teachers.

56
00:04:08,227 --> 00:04:09,527
Are they your mom's friends?

57
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:11,827
They went to an arts high school together.

58
00:04:15,727 --> 00:04:16,960
So,

59
00:04:17,394 --> 00:04:22,460
our teachers, our art instructors,
even contest judges,

60
00:04:24,194 --> 00:04:25,694
they're all your mom's friends?

61
00:04:26,594 --> 00:04:29,394
- Not all of them...
- That's why you're always first!

62
00:04:30,594 --> 00:04:31,894
Isn't that corruption?

63
00:04:32,627 --> 00:04:35,060
Do Hee, it's not like that.

64
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:37,827
They've known you since you were little.

65
00:04:38,294 --> 00:04:39,760
They've taught you.

66
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:42,727
Even Ms. Kim Yeong Seo taught you, right?

67
00:04:42,860 --> 00:04:44,060
No way!

68
00:04:44,227 --> 00:04:45,627
I had no idea.

69
00:04:46,194 --> 00:04:47,660
I thought you were a genius!

70
00:04:49,194 --> 00:04:51,960
If my mom finds out, she'll flip.

71
00:04:52,027 --> 00:04:53,627
Hey, we said it's a secret.

72
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,394
We promised to keep it between us.

73
00:04:55,494 --> 00:04:57,427
That only applies
when it doesn't screw me over.

74
00:04:58,260 --> 00:05:01,094
These bruises haven't even healed,
and you're still at it.

75
00:05:16,260 --> 00:05:19,127
- Do Hee!
- You're already number one anyway.

76
00:05:19,460 --> 00:05:23,860
- Even if you blow it, you're still first.
- Why are you like this? You got it wrong.

77
00:05:25,694 --> 00:05:28,927
You psycho, what's the mistake?
The mistake was me coming in second.

78
00:05:28,994 --> 00:05:32,660
- I'm just fixing it now.
- Do Hee, please!

79
00:05:32,727 --> 00:05:34,494
It's not fair. This is so unfair!

80
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:36,860
How am I supposed to deal with this?

81
00:05:40,827 --> 00:05:44,065
Does it hurt? Yeah, it hurt for me too.

82
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,727
Try getting hit all the time.

83
00:05:45,894 --> 00:05:47,427
You get stronger
without even realizing it.

84
00:05:48,427 --> 00:05:50,327
I had to learn to protect myself.

85
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:55,294
You'll get stronger too. Just wait.

86
00:06:31,060 --> 00:06:33,994
Poor thing. What now?

87
00:06:34,027 --> 00:06:36,260
- That hit her hard.
- Hey, did you hear that?

88
00:06:36,294 --> 00:06:39,494
- We didn't know you were there. Sorry.
- Sorry.

89
00:06:39,727 --> 00:06:43,860
- You must be freezing.
- You might catch a cold.

90
00:06:55,027 --> 00:06:59,493
I thought it was over
and that I had moved on,

91
00:06:59,494 --> 00:07:03,394
but my body still remembers everything.

92
00:07:30,294 --> 00:07:32,327
(Born with a silver spoon, Na Ji Ni)

93
00:07:33,394 --> 00:07:34,527
(Na Ji Ni, tell the truth and drop out.)

94
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:36,327
(Crazy psycho)

95
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:40,927
(Practical exam cheater)

96
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:05,527
In the end, I dropped out.

97
00:08:07,027 --> 00:08:09,160
But that wasn't the only reason.

98
00:08:10,494 --> 00:08:14,627
My happy path in life
ended in kindergarten.

99
00:08:15,194 --> 00:08:17,360
(Liebe Vocal Class)

100
00:08:35,994 --> 00:08:37,960
- The sun's up.
- Already?

101
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:39,394
We're running out of time.

102
00:08:41,760 --> 00:08:43,794
You drew this well.

103
00:08:44,027 --> 00:08:47,894
I've never seen Sleeping Beauty
look so full of life.

104
00:08:48,127 --> 00:08:49,927
She always seemed too passive.

105
00:08:50,060 --> 00:08:51,960
I actually liked that about her.

106
00:08:52,327 --> 00:08:54,427
A princess awakened by an unexpected kiss.

107
00:08:54,594 --> 00:08:57,027
- Isn't that nice and easy?
- What?

108
00:08:57,660 --> 00:09:01,127
Give up on The Little Mermaid.
Her whole life has been suffering.

109
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:04,460
Every step she takes hurts,
and if the prince knows who she is,

110
00:09:04,627 --> 00:09:05,760
she has to leave. Why choose to suffer?

111
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:08,360
She was the Sea King's daughter,
born with a silver spoon.

112
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:09,894
She just had bad luck.

113
00:09:09,960 --> 00:09:11,965
The Little Mermaid had bad luck?

114
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,060
I'm suddenly starving.
How about tteokbokki?

115
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:18,560
Right, about our dear aunt,

116
00:09:18,660 --> 00:09:21,427
- I wonder where she's hiding.
- That's what I'm saying.

117
00:09:21,494 --> 00:09:24,060
Who could she be waiting for,
taking this long?

118
00:09:24,302 --> 00:09:26,127
I told you I gave up.

119
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,127
You should give up too, Joong Bin.

120
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:31,060
- Hurry up before you end up like me.
- Okay.

121
00:09:31,327 --> 00:09:32,760
Get married and start your own business.

122
00:09:32,827 --> 00:09:35,094
- Why live trying to please others?
- General!

123
00:09:40,194 --> 00:09:41,226
Eat breakfast before you go.

124
00:09:41,227 --> 00:09:43,360
- I'll get it ready.
- What are you going to do?

125
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:47,767
Are you getting annoyed with me now?

126
00:09:48,005 --> 00:09:52,294
No, that's not it.
Why didn't you tell us...

127
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:54,375
Why make plans
when I'm making you breakfast?

128
00:09:54,527 --> 00:09:56,193
This is what happens
when we live together. Just bear with it.

129
00:09:56,194 --> 00:09:57,926
I let you live alone
hoping you'd finally get married,

130
00:09:57,927 --> 00:09:59,493
but you couldn't even do that
and came back home,

131
00:09:59,494 --> 00:10:01,294
so at least eat with your family.

132
00:10:03,394 --> 00:10:05,317
It's a Greek-style breakfast.

133
00:10:09,627 --> 00:10:12,762
- He even made the mousse himself.
- Okay.

134
00:10:12,894 --> 00:10:15,226
I was only going to nap
for 30 minutes and leave.

135
00:10:15,227 --> 00:10:18,665
Fine, let's have this
Greek-style breakfast.

136
00:10:19,160 --> 00:10:21,483
If you sleep for 30 minutes,
the next three days will be rough.

137
00:10:22,494 --> 00:10:23,537
Yes.

138
00:10:32,294 --> 00:10:34,027
We're done, right? Nothing's missing?

139
00:10:34,194 --> 00:10:35,326
I don't think so.

140
00:10:35,327 --> 00:10:37,693
Your memory is even better
than mine, General.

141
00:10:37,694 --> 00:10:39,328
Is that so?

142
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:48,296
Sun Kyung, you're up?

143
00:10:48,694 --> 00:10:49,894
Come out.

144
00:10:50,727 --> 00:10:52,627
Right. Did you sleep well?

145
00:10:53,327 --> 00:10:54,527
Pig.

146
00:10:58,160 --> 00:10:59,360
Didn't she sleep?

147
00:10:59,660 --> 00:11:01,160
Was I the only one who slept well?

148
00:11:04,760 --> 00:11:05,960
Thank you.

149
00:11:09,127 --> 00:11:10,527
Didn't you sleep last night?

150
00:11:11,227 --> 00:11:13,552
Your father slept like a pig.

151
00:11:14,494 --> 00:11:15,826
Dad, why did you do that?

152
00:11:15,827 --> 00:11:17,759
- You hurt Mom's feelings.
- You're right.

153
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,071
Why did I do that?

154
00:11:19,227 --> 00:11:21,760
Mom, eat a little and go back to sleep.

155
00:11:22,127 --> 00:11:23,327
Want me to stay with you?

156
00:11:23,394 --> 00:11:27,193
Such sweet words. I'm fine.

157
00:11:27,194 --> 00:11:29,127
Just hearing that
makes me feel well-rested.

158
00:11:29,527 --> 00:11:31,960
I'm meeting Do Hee
at the department store later.

159
00:11:32,294 --> 00:11:35,694
Talking with Do Hee
will make me feel better.

160
00:11:36,294 --> 00:11:37,560
Hurry up and get married.

161
00:11:37,694 --> 00:11:39,433
Do Hee is just what your mom needs.

162
00:11:42,394 --> 00:11:43,760
Why hasn't anyone said it's delicious?

163
00:11:43,794 --> 00:11:45,394
It's delicious. It's the best.

164
00:11:45,427 --> 00:11:46,627
It's just my people here.

165
00:11:47,427 --> 00:11:48,627
It's delicious.

166
00:11:48,694 --> 00:11:50,927
But eating too many vegetables
in the morning,

167
00:11:50,960 --> 00:11:52,760
can be hard to digest for some people,

168
00:11:52,827 --> 00:11:54,527
so eat a little, Sun Kyung.

169
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,560
Yes, Sa Bin.

170
00:11:56,707 --> 00:11:58,563
Yesterday,

171
00:11:58,760 --> 00:12:01,694
the woman reached out to me
and wants to see you a few more times.

172
00:12:02,253 --> 00:12:03,453
You're okay with that too, right?

173
00:12:04,694 --> 00:12:07,311
Yes, of course. I'd like to see her again.

174
00:12:18,927 --> 00:12:21,024
Your son at the international school
is doing well, right?

175
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:22,960
Of course.

176
00:12:23,494 --> 00:12:26,094
He came in third again.

177
00:12:26,494 --> 00:12:28,690
Really? Good for him.

178
00:12:29,327 --> 00:12:32,063
No matter how hard it is,
seeing your child succeed is worth it.

179
00:12:33,794 --> 00:12:35,794
How's your singer sister doing?

180
00:12:36,794 --> 00:12:41,460
Yes. But, General,
you said you'd call Assemblyman Kim...

181
00:12:42,594 --> 00:12:44,499
Is it already that late?

182
00:12:55,560 --> 00:12:56,760
Director Cha,

183
00:12:57,594 --> 00:12:58,865
the retest results are out.

184
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,560
Come to the hospital.

185
00:13:08,927 --> 00:13:10,127
Have a seat.

186
00:13:13,580 --> 00:13:14,780
That's all?

187
00:13:14,907 --> 00:13:16,954
I have to wear a dress
at the end of this month.

188
00:13:17,194 --> 00:13:20,380
If you're living with two women,
you should at least be considerate.

189
00:13:21,494 --> 00:13:23,160
You eat well when you're out.

190
00:13:23,527 --> 00:13:25,027
We're not young anymore.

191
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,933
It's time we started
taking care of breakfast.

192
00:13:26,994 --> 00:13:30,694
You've been going on
about your health lately, like an old man.

193
00:13:31,494 --> 00:13:34,272
Honey, let's stay young.

194
00:13:34,794 --> 00:13:37,393
I'm the one going through menopause.
What's gotten into you?

195
00:13:37,394 --> 00:13:38,427
Doctor Hwang...

196
00:13:38,494 --> 00:13:42,025
Doctors are always nagging their friends.
Just ignore him.

197
00:13:42,227 --> 00:13:45,294
It's chicken breast.

198
00:13:47,922 --> 00:13:49,149
Tonight,

199
00:13:49,229 --> 00:13:51,481
we have the orchestra team dinner.
You'll come, right?

200
00:13:51,494 --> 00:13:52,909
I can't. I have plans.

201
00:13:53,094 --> 00:13:54,494
You said you'd have time.

202
00:13:54,527 --> 00:13:56,160
Why did you suddenly make plans?

203
00:13:56,227 --> 00:13:57,560
Do I have to tell you everything?

204
00:13:57,960 --> 00:13:59,327
Am I your son?

205
00:13:59,360 --> 00:14:00,560
Honey.

206
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:07,910
- I'll come another time. I can't today.
- Come anyway.

207
00:14:08,513 --> 00:14:11,836
Ji Ni's busy, and now you too.
How am I supposed to live?

208
00:14:12,627 --> 00:14:14,127
When's that girl,

209
00:14:14,338 --> 00:14:16,438
going to make something of herself
through competitions?

210
00:14:16,527 --> 00:14:19,160
I told her to look into studying abroad
and becoming a professor,

211
00:14:19,161 --> 00:14:20,294
but she never listens.

212
00:14:20,327 --> 00:14:22,894
It's Ji Ni's life. Stop interfering.

213
00:14:22,994 --> 00:14:24,194
"Interfering?"

214
00:14:24,727 --> 00:14:26,284
You're being too much today.

215
00:14:27,027 --> 00:14:29,764
What's wrong with you?
Did you get a girlfriend?

216
00:14:29,927 --> 00:14:31,693
Or are you tired of this life?

217
00:14:31,694 --> 00:14:34,604
Yeah, I am.

218
00:14:35,707 --> 00:14:37,524
Where are you going? I'm talking to you.

219
00:14:37,860 --> 00:14:39,760
Come to the dinner, honey.

220
00:14:41,794 --> 00:14:44,212
Is he going through puberty?
Is he acting out?

221
00:14:46,052 --> 00:14:47,932
Did I feed him too much grass
or something?

222
00:14:48,094 --> 00:14:49,554
What does that mean?

223
00:14:49,694 --> 00:14:52,007
Director Cha, you need to be admitted.

224
00:14:52,227 --> 00:14:53,394
Cancel all your projects.

225
00:14:53,427 --> 00:14:55,868
No, I can't.
This one has a lot of overseas shoots.

226
00:14:55,869 --> 00:14:58,307
Is it serious? Am I dying?

227
00:14:59,060 --> 00:15:01,694
- Hey, I'm totally fine.
- No, you're not.

228
00:15:01,994 --> 00:15:04,160
This is your first checkup
in three years, right?

229
00:15:04,327 --> 00:15:05,827
I told you to do it every year.

230
00:15:05,866 --> 00:15:07,205
I've been busy.

231
00:15:08,294 --> 00:15:10,085
Is this why you told me
to come back for more tests?

232
00:15:12,207 --> 00:15:13,673
I was hoping it wasn't.

233
00:15:15,127 --> 00:15:16,427
Just tell me straight.

234
00:15:16,527 --> 00:15:18,500
Not as a patient, but as a friend.

235
00:15:18,794 --> 00:15:20,297
Don't hide anything.

236
00:15:21,327 --> 00:15:22,633
It's pancreatic cancer.

237
00:15:26,060 --> 00:15:30,117
It varies from person to person,
but you don't have much time.

238
00:15:30,394 --> 00:15:31,930
We'll try treatment,

239
00:15:32,960 --> 00:15:34,160
but this isn't something to take lightly.

240
00:15:37,876 --> 00:15:39,176
Still, the treatment...

241
00:15:39,494 --> 00:15:40,494
Forget it.

242
00:15:41,927 --> 00:15:43,242
I've got a year, right?

243
00:15:43,827 --> 00:15:46,842
Not something like three months?

244
00:15:47,894 --> 00:15:49,370
It could be even shorter.

245
00:15:55,194 --> 00:15:56,394
You bastard...

246
00:16:15,380 --> 00:16:17,688
As long as you receive proper treatment,
you'll make a quick recovery.

247
00:16:18,127 --> 00:16:19,327
They said you're all better.

248
00:16:19,827 --> 00:16:21,127
You don't have to come
to the hospital anymore.

249
00:17:20,573 --> 00:17:21,889
- Enjoy your meal.
- Thank you.

250
00:17:22,094 --> 00:17:24,736
I told you from the start
the weather was bad today.

251
00:17:24,750 --> 00:17:26,307
We shouldn't have come to the mountain.

252
00:17:26,394 --> 00:17:27,994
I knew this would happen.

253
00:17:28,694 --> 00:17:30,027
This isn't so bad though.

254
00:17:30,260 --> 00:17:31,960
Feels like skipping school.

255
00:17:34,027 --> 00:17:35,294
My goodness!

256
00:17:36,087 --> 00:17:37,353
Seriously...

257
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:38,727
You're such a scaredy-cat.

258
00:17:38,827 --> 00:17:41,627
Don't worry, guys.
I'll be the one struck by lightning.

259
00:17:41,694 --> 00:17:43,327
How do you live being scared of lightning?

260
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:45,394
You get struck once or twice in life.

261
00:17:46,127 --> 00:17:47,560
That mouth of yours...

262
00:17:47,960 --> 00:17:49,794
You'd be likable
if you'd just keep quiet.

263
00:17:55,627 --> 00:17:57,369
I really got struck...

264
00:18:03,819 --> 00:18:05,112
(Missed Call from My Love)

265
00:18:08,388 --> 00:18:09,667
(My Love)

266
00:18:14,558 --> 00:18:16,560
- Hello?
- Are you seriously cheating on me?

267
00:18:16,594 --> 00:18:19,193
Why aren't you answering your phone?
Where are you?

268
00:18:19,194 --> 00:18:21,359
I told you we had plans tonight.

269
00:18:21,360 --> 00:18:23,194
And I said I couldn't make it.

270
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:25,759
Why is everything on your terms?
Am I your servant?

271
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:27,294
Just leave me alone.

272
00:18:27,327 --> 00:18:30,011
Stop stressing me and Ji Ni out!

273
00:19:00,927 --> 00:19:02,866
Why me?

274
00:19:04,148 --> 00:19:05,439
Why?

275
00:19:06,694 --> 00:19:08,119
Why?

276
00:19:16,594 --> 00:19:17,794
Why?

277
00:19:29,694 --> 00:19:30,894
Your father-in-law?

278
00:19:31,724 --> 00:19:36,560
Yeah. Seung Hyun said his father
passed away when he was very young.

279
00:19:37,148 --> 00:19:39,148
When's the memorial date?

280
00:19:39,227 --> 00:19:41,794
Why are you suddenly curious?

281
00:19:42,727 --> 00:19:44,960
Did your dad in Ho Chi Minh City
ask you to?

282
00:19:44,994 --> 00:19:47,894
No, my mom was wondering too
when I visited last time.

283
00:19:47,961 --> 00:19:51,861
I see. That makes sense.

284
00:19:52,049 --> 00:19:55,464
You don't even hold a memorial for him,
just for the grandparents.

285
00:19:56,604 --> 00:19:59,594
Were you divorced?

286
00:20:00,795 --> 00:20:01,822
Yeah.

287
00:20:02,674 --> 00:20:06,221
Seung Hyun wasn't comfortable about it,
so he said his dad had passed away.

288
00:20:08,717 --> 00:20:09,717
Then does that mean...

289
00:20:09,796 --> 00:20:15,303
you still hold memorial rites
for your ex-husband's father?

290
00:20:15,704 --> 00:20:20,001
- Mother, you're really kind.
- Then treat me well if you know that.

291
00:20:21,503 --> 00:20:22,902
What should we have for dinner?

292
00:20:24,227 --> 00:20:26,271
I feel dizzy from all the greasy smell.

293
00:20:26,273 --> 00:20:29,695
Then should I make some noodles?

294
00:20:29,787 --> 00:20:31,111
Yeah, let's do that.

295
00:20:42,767 --> 00:20:44,337
Is O Reum still sleeping?

296
00:20:55,463 --> 00:20:56,708
She must've held back for a long time,

297
00:20:57,666 --> 00:20:59,097
if she's only asking now.

298
00:21:01,125 --> 00:21:02,691
I guess it can't be helped.

299
00:21:25,677 --> 00:21:29,349
Mai! I told you not to do that!

300
00:21:30,958 --> 00:21:33,311
If I don't, it brings bad luck.

301
00:21:33,410 --> 00:21:36,925
O Reum is Korean,
but he's also Vietnamese.

302
00:21:36,971 --> 00:21:39,290
- And I'm his mother.
- Yeah, I know.

303
00:21:39,336 --> 00:21:43,211
- I know he's your son.
- I know you don't like it,

304
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:46,173
but I can't give this up.

305
00:21:46,488 --> 00:21:48,211
This protects O Reum.

306
00:21:48,232 --> 00:21:51,791
That doesn't make any sense.
How is that protecting him?

307
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:54,088
It really gives me the creeps.

308
00:21:54,334 --> 00:21:57,296
Why put a knife
by a sleeping child's head?

309
00:21:57,400 --> 00:22:00,648
He won't get hurt.
I've never seen a child get hurt.

310
00:22:00,650 --> 00:22:02,809
Anyway, this is my order.

311
00:22:03,748 --> 00:22:05,050
I can't allow this.

312
00:22:05,347 --> 00:22:06,356
Not this.

313
00:22:07,593 --> 00:22:11,671
Do it in Vietnam if you want, not here.

314
00:22:11,673 --> 00:22:14,536
If anything bad happens to O Reum,
it's on you.

315
00:22:15,738 --> 00:22:17,843
Fine. Then it's my fault.

316
00:22:19,269 --> 00:22:21,554
Give it to me. I'll put it away.

317
00:22:22,294 --> 00:22:24,192
How could you put...

318
00:22:24,194 --> 00:22:26,047
a hideous knife like this
by a child's bed?

319
00:22:26,049 --> 00:22:29,955
Mother, don't speak carelessly
about another country's traditions.

320
00:22:29,957 --> 00:22:31,756
That's very rude.

321
00:22:32,117 --> 00:22:35,470
I'm really offended.
It feels like you're looking down on me.

322
00:22:38,273 --> 00:22:39,797
Okay. I'm sorry.

323
00:22:40,131 --> 00:22:42,176
But I never looked down on your country.

324
00:22:42,624 --> 00:22:46,899
If I did, would I have accepted you
and let you go clubbing all night?

325
00:22:50,839 --> 00:22:54,202
- Dad's here.
- Mrs. Yeong Ju, I'm home.

326
00:23:02,405 --> 00:23:05,991
Let them be.
They can raise their own child.

327
00:23:06,366 --> 00:23:09,915
You raised the two of us
the way you wanted.

328
00:23:10,060 --> 00:23:11,600
O Reum is my child too.

329
00:23:11,667 --> 00:23:12,671
Yes.

330
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:14,161
He is your child.

331
00:23:15,604 --> 00:23:18,909
Mom, you're being really annoying.
Why are you so obsessed?

332
00:23:19,049 --> 00:23:20,606
Mai will take care of it.

333
00:23:20,651 --> 00:23:23,030
- They said no one got hurt.
- It's a knife.

334
00:23:23,075 --> 00:23:24,398
How can I just let it go?

335
00:23:25,049 --> 00:23:27,302
I even let her stay out
all night at clubs.

336
00:23:27,832 --> 00:23:29,442
I'm her mother-in-law in name only.

337
00:23:29,444 --> 00:23:31,603
I've let her do as she pleases
without saying a word.

338
00:23:32,383 --> 00:23:35,658
And who speaks to her mother-in-law
like that these days?

339
00:23:36,761 --> 00:23:39,408
Mom, you said a daughter-in-law
is your child too.

340
00:23:39,755 --> 00:23:41,664
Do daughters speak formally
to their mothers?

341
00:23:41,666 --> 00:23:44,875
- Cha Seung Woo!
- See? You get angry when you're losing.

342
00:23:45,671 --> 00:23:47,701
What you're saying doesn't make sense.

343
00:23:48,641 --> 00:23:51,954
If she's your Vietnamese daughter-in-law,
accept Vietnamese culture too.

344
00:23:52,284 --> 00:23:54,997
And if she's your daughter,
speaking casually is fine.

345
00:23:55,342 --> 00:23:56,968
It's not like she means it badly.

346
00:23:58,518 --> 00:24:01,940
She only pushes back like that
because she wants to live with us.

347
00:24:02,015 --> 00:24:05,293
If she wanted to leave,
she wouldn't argue. Right?

348
00:24:10,662 --> 00:24:13,284
My dear Yeong Ju,

349
00:24:13,286 --> 00:24:18,511
who never cries,
even when she's lonely or sad.

350
00:24:18,955 --> 00:24:20,455
Move. It's hot.

351
00:24:22,624 --> 00:24:23,767
Go to your room.

352
00:24:24,148 --> 00:24:25,944
Change and wash up. You smell like sweat.

353
00:24:32,993 --> 00:24:36,486
Mom, you get a little sensitive
around Grandpa's memorial day.

354
00:24:36,876 --> 00:24:40,900
We know how you feel, but Mai doesn't.
Please understand.

355
00:24:41,523 --> 00:24:43,557
It's hard on Seung Hyun,
being stuck in the middle.

356
00:24:55,005 --> 00:24:56,491
I'm cursed with bad luck.

357
00:24:56,967 --> 00:24:58,807
I don't even have luck
with my daughter-in-law.

358
00:25:07,408 --> 00:25:10,441
Now I even have a daughter-in-law
I can't communicate with, Father.

359
00:25:11,818 --> 00:25:15,407
I'm so hurt because of you, Father.

360
00:25:22,642 --> 00:25:23,656
Honey!

361
00:25:26,308 --> 00:25:29,523
Say that again. Where are you going?

362
00:25:30,443 --> 00:25:33,376
- Where did you say you're going?
- It's my father's memorial.

363
00:25:33,524 --> 00:25:35,136
I should go now.

364
00:25:35,482 --> 00:25:37,044
How could you say that?

365
00:25:37,126 --> 00:25:39,313
- Se Ri, please listen to me.
- Stay away from me.

366
00:25:40,853 --> 00:25:43,197
How could you do this to me?

367
00:25:44,993 --> 00:25:48,590
Is that why you've been
so distant all this time?

368
00:25:48,592 --> 00:25:51,961
- That's not it.
- So this is how it ends?

369
00:25:52,311 --> 00:25:56,903
After everything I did to survive,
this is what I get!

370
00:26:01,285 --> 00:26:05,205
- What's wrong with you?
- Let go! I'll end it all.

371
00:26:06,574 --> 00:26:10,200
I can't live like this. Go.

372
00:26:10,919 --> 00:26:12,607
Do whatever you want.

373
00:26:12,634 --> 00:26:14,702
I'll do whatever I want too.

374
00:26:15,503 --> 00:26:16,809
I'll kill myself.

375
00:26:18,015 --> 00:26:23,562
Cha Min Ki, if loving you led to this,
I'll take revenge from the grave.

376
00:26:23,564 --> 00:26:25,316
Please stop this.

377
00:26:25,679 --> 00:26:27,688
I'm the one who wants to die!

378
00:26:29,249 --> 00:26:31,994
When will it ever be enough for you?

379
00:26:31,996 --> 00:26:33,793
What I wear, what I eat and how I live.

380
00:26:34,499 --> 00:26:36,588
I've done everything your way
my whole life.

381
00:26:36,827 --> 00:26:38,299
Please give in just this once.

382
00:26:39,130 --> 00:26:41,236
I could go without telling you.

383
00:26:41,405 --> 00:26:44,403
But that wouldn't be right
because we're married.

384
00:26:45,774 --> 00:26:49,604
Fine. Go. I won't stop you.

385
00:26:51,353 --> 00:26:53,888
You say you're only going
to pay your respects.

386
00:26:56,927 --> 00:26:59,226
Do you think I don't know
why you suddenly want to go,

387
00:26:59,228 --> 00:27:02,193
to your father's memorial
after all these years?

388
00:27:04,133 --> 00:27:06,352
I know everything.

389
00:27:07,219 --> 00:27:11,508
Go. I said I won't stop you.

390
00:27:12,854 --> 00:27:15,848
- Stop it!
- Let go!

391
00:27:25,666 --> 00:27:31,198
We're a mess.
No wonder you can't stand this anymore.

392
00:27:31,569 --> 00:27:33,998
- Se Ri.
- End it all.

393
00:27:36,490 --> 00:27:40,499
- Please, just stop!
- Let go!

394
00:27:50,862 --> 00:27:51,907
Honey!

395
00:27:57,937 --> 00:27:59,072
Honey!

396
00:28:17,428 --> 00:28:20,704
(Family Register)

397
00:28:20,816 --> 00:28:23,716
I fell in love with someone
I never should have loved.

398
00:28:23,718 --> 00:28:26,202
- How could you?
- How could you do this to me, Mom?

399
00:28:26,204 --> 00:28:28,884
She should be blacklisted
from the art world.

400
00:28:28,886 --> 00:28:30,384
You'll reject her painting, right?

401
00:28:30,386 --> 00:28:32,770
No wonder mom loses it
when you act like this, Dad.

402
00:28:32,771 --> 00:28:35,093
Mom asks me to understand her.
Dad asks me to understand him.

403
00:28:35,095 --> 00:28:37,285
So who am I supposed to ask
to understand me?

404
00:28:37,287 --> 00:28:39,443
Move. It's my house. Why can't I come in?

405
00:28:39,444 --> 00:28:42,806
What is going on? You two, you!

406
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,000
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
